'''Rose Arce''' is Executive Producer of Starfish Media Group, the production company of television journalist Soledad O'Brien. She was formerly a Senior Producer at [[CNN]].<ref name='wagz'/> Arce graduated from [[Barnard College]] in 1986.<ref name=barnard/> She shared a [[Pulitzer Prize]] in 1992 as well as <!--shared?--> three [[Emmy]]s for news reporting.<ref name=wagz/>
==Awards==
In 1991 Arce was a member{{citation needed|date=November 2013}} of the staff that covered the [[1991 Union Square derailment]] for ''[[New York Newsday]]''. They won the 1992 [[Pulitzer Prize for Spot News Reporting]] for their "coverage of a midnight subway derailment in Manhattan that left five passengers dead and more than 200 injured."<ref name=pulitzer>[http://www.pulitzer.org/bycat/Spot-News-Reporting "Spot News Reporting"]. The Pulitzer Prizes. Retrieved 2013-11-06.</ref>
==Books==
